@startuml
title UPVEST Entire System Architecture

left to right direction

actor User

package "Frontend (Browser)" {
  component "Web UI" as UI
  component "Static Assets" as Assets
}

package "Backend Services" {
  component "API Server (FastAPI)" as API
  component "Auth Manager" as Auth
  component "Trading Engine" as Engine
  component "AI Decision Engine" as AI
  component "Strategy Engine" as Strat
  component "Market Data Fetcher" as Data
  component "Database Manager" as DB
  component "Risk Manager" as Risk
  component "Trading Mode Manager" as Mode
  component "Upstox Connector" as Upstox
}

package "AI/ML" {
  component "Feature Engineering" as FE
  component "LSTM Models (daily/intraday)" as Models
  component "Sentiment & RL" as OtherAI
  database "Trained Models" as ModelStore
}

package "External Resources" {
  database "Upstox API / Live Market" as LiveMarket
  database "Historical Data DB" as HistDB
}

User --> UI : interact via browser
UI --> API : REST requests (start/stop, status, predictions)

API --> Auth : validate users / tokens
API --> Engine : place orders, check status, query portfolio
API --> AI : request price prediction / decision
API --> Data : obtain latest/historical candles
API --> DB : read/write trades and state

Engine --> Mode : determine paper/live
Engine --> Risk : check limits
Engine --> Upstox : send orders / fetch positions
Engine --> DB : record trades, update balances

AI --> FE : prepare features
AI --> Models : load & run LSTM
AI --> OtherAI : sentiment / reinforcement signals
Models --> ModelStore : read weights

Data --> LiveMarket : pull realtime quotes
Data --> HistDB : cache history

DB --> HistDB : store historical candles & logs

Upstox --> LiveMarket : external API calls

' optional arrows indicating feedback
AI --> DB : store predictions
Strat --> API : strategy signals

note right of API: Orchestrates modules,
handles CORS, authentication,
and exposes "/api/ai/predict"

note bottom: System is modular; each component
is a Python module under project root.

@enduml